cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on sentence simplification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses a deep reinforcement learning framework to address the simplification problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses an encoder-decoder model to generate simplified sentences. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to learn simplification rewrites. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents a new model for sentence simplification.
